Jenkins Installation on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu)This project provides a step-by-step guide to deploying a persistent Jenkins CI/CD server on an Amazon EC2 instance running Ubuntu.
ğŸ“‹ PrerequisitesAn 
AWS Account.
An EC2 Instance (Recommended: t3.small or larger with 2GB+ RAM).
MobaXterm or SSH client installed.A Key Pair (.pem file) for SSH access.

ğŸ›¡ï¸ Step 1: Security Group Configuration
Before connecting, ensure your EC2 Security Group has the following Inbound Rules:
Protocol   Port   Source    Description
SSH,       22     My IP     Secure terminal access
TCP,       8080   0.0.0.0/0  Jenkins Web Interface


ğŸš€ Step 2: Installation Script.
Connect to your instance via SSH (Username: ubuntu) and execute the following commands:
1. Update System & Install Java
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install fontconfig openjdk-17-jre -y

2. Add Jenkins Repository
sudo wget -O /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/" | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

3.Install and Start Jenkins
sudo apt update
sudo apt install jenkins -y
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins

ğŸ”‘ Step 3: Unlock Jenkins
1.Open your browser and navigate to http://<YOUR-EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:8080.
2.To retrieve the initial administrator password, run:
Bash

sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
3.Copy the output and paste it into the Jenkins "Unlock" screen.
4.Select "Install Suggested Plugins" and create your admin user.


ğŸ“‚ Troubleshooting & Paths
Check Status: sudo systemctl status jenkins
Restart Jenkins: sudo systemctl restart jenkins
View Logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/jenkins/jenkins.log
Home Directory: /var/lib/jenkins
